{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing agent tracking behavior**\\n\\nI'm wondering if the agent only tracks when it triggers a new class initialization and if it instruments methods accordingly. It seems like coverage might only check for return results in the metadata. If the class is already loaded, there may be no metadata available.\\n\\nTo ensure dynamic access to metadata, I think I should use a library class that isn’t loaded yet. However, since the test uses the RestAssured class, which is definitely loaded, it raises some questions. I need to look into whether `DYNAMICALLY_LOADED_CLASS_NAME` isn’t loaded, particularly with how `FileReader` is used.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_snUIGPDY9YY7dBcm7H03woVn|fc_0db716c3ad0b818b016a2815b71b5081948cf189ac59b11e05", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "metadata/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/reachability-metadata.json", "limit": 200}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1676, "output": 1215, "cacheRead": 57344, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 60235, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781011856628, "responseId": "resp_0db716c3ad0b818b016a2815914e0c8194a804b23924c87705"}}
