[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating coverage tests**\n\nI’m considering that maybe the external report attempts didn’t include our local state, even though the user mentioned that two attempts were made after some changes to their workflow. I’m wondering if the tests actually need to include the artificial calls separately; the coverage tool may filter out \"Class.forName\" call sites invoked through reflection. Direct reflection should still be counted, but maybe the agent doesn’t attribute the source call site when invoked reflectively?\n\n**Evaluating test compilation issues**\n\nI'm considering a potential issue with how Javac compiles Java tests. It seems our new test file has a `$` in a string, which might be okay, but the test class isn't currently tracked. I wonder if the user might rerun on the base that excludes our file? Perhaps we should update the existing `CsrfTokenFinderTest` instead of creating a new one. I think it’s worth checking if the active class name matches the file mapping to ensure tests are executed properly. If they pass, that means everything worked.\n\n**Investigating CSRF token handling**\n\nI’m thinking that perhaps `CsrfTokenFinder.findInHtml` is only used when calling `.csrf(uri)`, but Rest Assured might have issues parsing HTML due to a missing HTML parser. The existing `CsrfTokenFinderTest` probably passes as our behavior is similar. I should check the upstream Rest Assured CSRF API and see if the `.csrf(baseUri)` method affects header prioritization.\n\nI wonder if I can call `class$` from within the closure's `doCall` since it currently uses ldc constants. Maybe it's an unused helper or a fallback for Groovy pre-Java5? But it seems I need to check if the method is synthetic or private, which could help clarify how to approach this.\n\n**Analyzing agent tracking behavior**\n\nI'm wondering if the agent only tracks when it triggers a new class initialization and if it instruments methods accordingly. It seems like coverage might only check for return results in the metadata. If the class is already loaded, there may be no metadata available.\n\nTo ensure dynamic access to metadata, I think I should use a library class that isn’t loaded yet. However, since the test uses the RestAssured class, which is definitely loaded, it raises some questions. I need to look into whether `DYNAMICALLY_LOADED_CLASS_NAME` isn’t loaded, particularly with how `FileReader` is used.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0db716c3ad0b818b016a2815925b008194ae720f3ba68670ed\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKBW373uvFzDH6P-rY3e_5rbQFMczVxVxuHD3XP9gbhZX-2WyOVVIiAhjUSVBR9jVgqOVOF-AyJ2wgRo1CbgJYL4x-RvF5-1oPyOJ1dS8jdkFtE3v6XydQIQTubpgorSme4rsSRY9hJRYSQs80Nmhj6Ncu7XKxX6UE_xGcvg2APaAakUuHhfzi7V3jXTN13gmu_l9LVGyRJjumLX0PQMeJU-fcvaE23EZ3CiTjK3YV2Lf3tpoOkV6kjbvac9fRjN8f6slfqF5eAGDSplszA5zRvJqmnhtirSdPsWPr0Fyb-MQVBPpX3tCl2dLDk5g4dauCr9vVpYVfvvLBPK9_FRQUYvOcuFrhBZ7qqBdtWnHGfqQa0ZNouaTE-IT4OQpTolaAS709Ttjmg_5TNPf3gGSsJnC-6b-I3eE0lh4E_uBqDWE_DmDa9eueb5w67VAcgSz49B0hFkKVuDEuAjEuHT_QSSN1A-wcbf4J1igoVuRJRRlyz3PiH7heKx2lNAnLu3f35HKBK-zEAOSE06IPGR1gPHyZQ210FRkRvA1emaCz-kvCGxaHCPtxdiJEAPuQlSyl7grgQTl6tvmMv21Z67B2pM0dGgo_64L11kGIHSW2IWXn4mB79gz3mUbhpZzSrgDaLmiFi4125se0Wq4xmZvY3IxIKozABEprxMKWf3g7iO0KGrI_KG7f3tYl0pepmttgo-nTuI7wQnS7b6aHs5LOmTgu2aIYm71KL41_yse9YUBevDjQm1iakvPnY-B44_muXKJ1eaPfGpUM3WvinIc1MezYIAcfrzTgKbw-To6P4Hwq85TnFujnlv21yDKVQax670I7tOub5Bs3d4XckC3s5zZxVQxtECSj_4sj0galIfYePNm9Xw6g1LxQTR-0Z5vUiKb2O1pGIUbclcjF8CErkQ2PEJ0AKr8ZD3IOoEGpEW8LbceBnjstb25663P2-YNQyaGHjqseHUQFeNDCsoZA8TRK-Y1HdW6UOwoWQD5GlKDhARDzv8UHev2iDR91yNNUNFuS76wcs8xIfTplBhpt5KyZuUntIgeXJIDNIFgZL6giTdTUYrm3uG9lbG03qwGk5ThRmwFZtEYkwr2Sdp2e4VhiAcRMRm63Kh7Dtv9LoikZV_IWAkDeFfzKFxHILTXvnaHUoTVg6KSd-SlRzfKERa5ogmvZDZoXmklxXBq9vzD7nVGA_iPLzsmFndEJYNGkNJtGD5pDimNROILaun-86D5-a4btZbjW2cbL5-X69qw8LeBKt8EMCkdI7Dz_JnZRveJUvxeEeYpftJyhrM88ffEfUwSHIpFGHAN6